{"name":"Earthmother's Tear","type":"consumable","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Earthmother%27s%20Tear.PNG","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>When the Earthmother's Blessing and Mist Tear, are smashed together, the hatred of all living creatures will be felt by the user, and for a brief time, after consumption, you'll feel immortal, but at a cost...</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>When the potion is consumed, a small crystal appears at the creature's feet and starts to glow with a blue tint, as it does, the transformation into a Lich begins. The flesh of the user starts to decay and scorch, as blue flames engulf the creature, leaving behind a walking corpse. All creatures in <strong>20 feet</strong> of the caster will need to do a <strong>DC 10 Wisdom</strong> saving throw against this magic or become frightened for a minute. When the transformation is complete, the creature statblock is replaced by one of a @Compendium[dnd5e.monsters.bfh29vIEoGzI240e]{Lich}, and it lasts for 1 minute. After which, the crystal will lose its glow and become inert. The crystal can be used in the process of creating a @Compendium[dnd5e.monsters.bfh29vIEoGzI240e]{Lich}.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The target assumes the hit points of its new form. When it reverts to its normal form, the creature returns to the half number of hit points it had before it transformed. The creature's maximum hit points will also be reduced by half, not gaining any benefits from short or long rests. This can be reverted by @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.qLeEXZDbW5y4bmLY]{True Resurrection} or by the creature becoming a Lich permanently.</p>\n<p> </p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":1000,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OAPsZ8fH2KsnU1r9"}},"_id":"7zsBv9WnyZVroAWZ"}
{"name":"Book of Transferred Ascension","type":"consumable","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Book%20of%20Transferred%20Ascension.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>A series of books that were forgotten about for centuries, were created for the sole purpose to teach the new scholars or students magical and physical classes and skills without having a heavy time investment in learning them. From what is known about these books, the owner of a spell with clear indications can teach anybody a spell, skill, or even something as common as fishing. As the books are magical in nature, the user has to create a strong bond with it and as the new pupil learns the new skill the book will crumble to dust.</em>  </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Use: During 14 days period of downtime, without interruption in a safe area town, city, fort, village, etc. the user who attuned this book can teach one of his spells to a different PC. These books cannot be used while traveling, as it requires full concentration from both parties, if the training is interrupted, it has to be restarted. The user then can copy one of his spells, however, it has to be used with the original intent. If a spell is cast, it has to use the spellcasting modifier from the transferring user. Example: If a spell is transferred from a Sorcerer to a Wizard, the Wizard will have to use CHA for his spellcasting ability. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>This book be only used to transfer magical spells between two users.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium Of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2000,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"day","cost":14,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":14,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true},"consume":{"type":"charges","target":"","amount":1},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"scroll"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lOB28wvaPTaYlH8y"}},"_id":"LvJcfkbWz0upnuke"}
{"name":"Sky Dew","type":"consumable","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Sky%20Dew.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>It is rumored this orb comes from a set of four, their existence as old as time itself. The blue orb is stipulated to contain a liquid that will restore anyone to his most fit force. After consumption, it is believed that another copy of the orb appears somewhere else in the world.</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Use: The orb needs to be shattered and the contents drunk. When the contents are consumed restore the character to<strong> full HP</strong>. If the item is consumed the character will not gain any benefits from any short rests up until a long rest is completed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"price":500,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true},"consume":{"type":"charges","target":"","amount":1},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mWFdUkM3cq4l55j7"}},"_id":"OzIaFXS8FMbdl1Av"}
{"_id":"Q4uOjwRkwwghDc69","name":"Mist Tear","type":"consumable","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Mist%20Tear.PNG","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>It is rumored this orb comes from a set of four, their existence as old as time itself. It is believed that the purple orb, which seems to be slowly pulsating and the fluid in it seems to be perpetually moving, contains one of the most potent acids in existence.  After its destruction, it is believed that another copy of the orb appears somewhere else in the world.</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Use:</strong> As an action, you can throw this orb up to <strong>60 feet</strong>, shattering it on impact. Make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the Mist Tear orb as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes  <strong>8d4 fire damage</strong> at the start of each of its turns. A creature can end this damage by using its action to make a <strong>DC 14 Dexterity</strong> check to extinguish the flames.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"price":500,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":60,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true},"consume":{"type":"charges","target":"","amount":1},"ability":"dex","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[["8d4 +@mod","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tpSWcl5SplZUgBQu"}}}
{"name":"Earthmother's Dew","type":"consumable","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Earthmother%27s%20Dew.PNG","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>When the Earthmother's Blessing and Sky Dew, are smashed together, the primordial fires contained within one of the orbs, start to soothe, and as they merge an orb of blue power takes their place. Making the holder feel attuned with nature, for a brief second. If the contents of this orb are consumed, the original orbs and the newly formed one will disappear from existence, leaving no trace of them in all creatures’ collective memories.</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Use</strong>: If consumed by a creature, it will restore HP and all Hit Dice consumed to their original maximum value.</p>\n<p>If it is poured on a recently deceased creature. This potion closes all wounds, neutralizes any poison, and cures all diseases when they died. The potion replaces damaged or missing organs and limbs. If a creature is resurrected this way, the creature will not gain any benefits from short or long rests, up until a @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.TkJ8Wtg1L7TZtspm]{Dispel Evil and Good} is performed. The potion has no effect on already resurrected creatures or undead.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":1000,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"veryRare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.H3kp76rY9zW2owki"}},"_id":"URu1vPFZTV0a9iDF"}
{"name":"Chocolate Smore","type":"loot","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Chocolate%20Smore.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>It is rumored this orb comes from a set of four, their existence as old as time itself. This orb has several teeth and claws marks, however, its shape remained round even after years of misusage. After its destruction, it is believed that another copy of the orb appears somewhere else in the world.</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>The last owner of this orb was a Goblin named Clueless that appeared one day in town with a cat traveling by his side. The name was provided by the city folk since the Goblin was roaming aimlessly shouting in gibberish while praising the round rock and randomly stating that it is chocolate. Eventually, a trader has decided to get it off his hands for a piece of silver. Now Clueless is cherishing and praising his new coin possession.</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>The trader had the peculiar round rock investigated, but besides its indestructible state, after a blacksmith attempted to smash it with hammers and weapons, nothing else stands out. </em></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0.01,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"common","identified":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wIM0mmdJTzhbAQ7e"}},"_id":"oUu0VFPD0ssm35j8"}
{"name":"Earthmother's Blessing","type":"consumable","img":"modules/kctg-common/images/Earthmother%27s%20Blessing.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>It is rumored this orb comes from a set of four, their existence as old as time itself. This orb is a bit warm to the touch, does feel like it's pulsating at steady intervals. After its usage, it is believed that another copy of the orb appears somewhere else in the world.</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Use:</strong> As an action, an attempt to throw this orb can be performed. A <strong>flat DC 10</strong> check needs to be passed. If successful, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the Earthmother's Blessing orb as an improvised weapon. On a hit summon an @Compendium[dnd5e.monsters.sApYLZj9PTZ40wJr]{Earth Elemental} and a @Compendium[dnd5e.monsters.8SMQl75HLjhuSeau]{Fire Elemental} next to the target. On a miss, the summons will be 15 feet away from the user and on the failed flat check, the orb will burst due to its agitation and spawn the creatures next to the user.</p>\n<p>Summon a  and a </p>\n<p>The elementals will be hostile towards all targets, PCs, and NPCs, attacking from the closest to the furthest away.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Kris's Compendium of Trade Goods","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":500,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true},"consume":{"type":"charges","target":"","amount":1},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"wand"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"npRNSqPYXpT1U5Rk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wnuX4u3DSvwG1rYs"}},"_id":"ogzs5zWM0RPCktlM"}
